  <hidden>true</hidden>
  <content>Example:

##{{{{{kanban app="Ideas" category="priority" order="doc.date" columns="status,assignement" /}}}}}##

* ##app or className## application or className for which to build the kanban board
* ##category## field to use to break down the kanban board
* ##xwql## additional xwql to restrict the query
* ##order## field by which to order cards
* ##title## field to display the title
* ##columns## additional columns to display 
* ##cssClasses## classes to display the columns. Default is col-xs-12 col-md-4

The Kanban macro allows to drag and drop items from one column to another.

Examples:

== Kanban of Ideas by priority with status and assignement fields ==

{{kanban app="Ideas" category="priority" order="doc.date" columns="status,assignement" /}}

== Kanban of Ideas by priority with status and assignement fields only open Ideas ==

{{kanban app="Ideas" category="priority" order="doc.date" columns="status,assignement" xwql="obj.status='open'" /}}

== Kanban of Ideas by priority with assignement only open Ideas ==

{{kanban app="Ideas" category="assignement" order="doc.date" columns="status,priority" xwql="obj.status='open'" /}}

== Kanban of Ideas by status without fields ==

{{kanban app="Ideas" category="status" order="status" /}}

== Kanban of Ideas by status with priority field ==

{{kanban app="Ideas" category="status" order="status" columns="priority" /}}

== Kanban of Ideas using class by priority ==

{{kanban className="Ideas.IdeasClass" category="priority" order="status" title="status" /}}
</content>
